<dec f='ffmpeg/libavcodec/avcodec.h' l='3979' type='void avcodec_flush_buffers(AVCodecContext * avctx)'/>
<doc f='ffmpeg/libavcodec/avcodec.h' l='3962'>/**
 * Reset the internal codec state / flush internal buffers. Should be called
 * e.g. when seeking or when switching to a different stream.
 *
 * @note for decoders, when refcounted frames are not used
 * (i.e. avctx-&gt;refcounted_frames is 0), this invalidates the frames previously
 * returned from the decoder. When refcounted frames are used, the decoder just
 * releases any references it might keep internally, but the caller&apos;s reference
 * remains valid.
 *
 * @note for encoders, this function will only do something if the encoder
 * declares support for AV_CODEC_CAP_ENCODER_FLUSH. When called, the encoder
 * will drain any remaining packets, and can then be re-used for a different
 * stream (as opposed to sending a null frame which will leave the encoder
 * in a permanent EOF state after draining). This can be desirable if the
 * cost of tearing down and replacing the encoder instance is high.
 */</doc>
